      {
        "id": 2544513,
        "name": "Ilkka |_ |_| mme",
        "username": "IlkkaL",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/ilkkal/{size}/2504_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-12-22T09:06:47.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>My first go with this producer that has gained solid praise around the Internets. Really fantastic value - on par with Bernard Moreau\u2019s 2015 as a very good Bourgogne Blanc that is offering a lot of pleasure already. Might be just luck but I\u2019ve been getting a lot of bang for the back from Burgundy lately.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>2015 Jean-Marc Vincent Bourgogne Blanc</strong> <em>- France, Burgundy, Bourgogne Blanc (22.12.2018)</em><br>\nA mighty classic C\u00f4te de Beaune nose here: powerful and generous with notes of lemon, oak, hazelnut, spice and a hint of butter. On the palate there is quite a volume and presence - this is no shy, timid wallflower. Loads of salty minerality and some spice as well. Bright-fruited with very good energy and acidity that leaves one\u2019s mouth watering. I must say this is a mighty complete wine and yet another 2015 that is not one bit fat despite some early generalizations.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
